-- Deep River of Mauritius Rises Most This Year on FUEL Merger
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-05-08T09:42:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/deep-river-of-mauritius-rises-most-this-year-on-fuel-merger.html
Deep River Beau Champ Ltd. (DRBC) , a
Mauritian sugar producer, rose the most this year after saying
directors approved its merger with Flacq United Estates Ltd.  The  stock  jumped 13 percent, the most since Dec. 28, to 26
rupees, the highest since April 9, by the close in  Port Louis ,
the capital.  The boards of the companies approved the merger of FUEL
into Deep River, according to cautionary announcements published
on the Stock Exchange of Mauritius’s  website  today. The merger
is “subject to the satisfaction of certain conditions including
the receipt of all relevant third party approvals,” they said.  The new entity vies to become the Indian Ocean island
nation’s largest sugar producer, with the two companies holding
a 36 percent share of total output in 2011, according to
preliminary data from the Mauritius Sugar Syndicate.  FUEL (FUEL)  shareholders will receive 0.9 share in Deep River for
each they already own. The target date for the completion of the
merger is June 30, according to the statements.  FUEL shares 
declined 5.2 percent, the most since April 23, to 25.50 rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
